@RestController
Spring Boot annotation.
tells to Spring:
👉 “This class will handle HTTP requests and return data as a response (like JSON).”


why @RestController
Build REST APIs
return data like JSON
Avoid writing extra code for @ResponseBody


 When is @RestController used?
 You want to return data (like JSON), not HTML pages.
  when someone sends a GET request to /all-types, you return a list of jewel types.



What is an “HTML view”?
In Spring Boot (or traditional Spring MVC), a view means an HTML page (or JSP/Thymeleaf page) that is shown in the browser.
